Sterna usually with a deep, narrow, longitudinal depression between coxae (
Fig. 2 F
), but sterna between coxae 6, 7 and 9 much wider (
Fig. 4 A
). Gonopod aperture transverse-oval, relatively small, far from reaching lateral sides of segment 7. Legs very short; tarsal segment longest; claw usual, simple, very slightly curved ventrad; some setae sparsely microdenticulate
(
Figs 2 F
;
3 E
)
